                        "description": "<p>Dissolved organic matter (DOM) was extracted from the leachate samples using a common solid-phase extraction protocol over 1&nbsp;g PPL resin<strong>[1]</strong>.</p><p><br></p><p>The full description will be published in a manuscript.</p><p>Liquid samples were subjected to SPE (Bond Elut PPL cartridge, 1 g, 6 mL, Agilent Technologies). LC-MS file formats are Thermo Scientific .raw files.</p><p><br></p><p>Leaf litter decomposition was traced with untargeted metabolomics (LC-MS; dataset here) side by side with other (metabolic) fingerprinting methods. A study manuscript is in preparation and will be connected to this entry upon publication.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Ref:</strong></p><p><strong>[1]</strong> Dittmar T, Koch B, Hertkorn N, Kattner G. A simple and efficient method for the solid-phase extraction of dissolved organic matter (SPE-DOM) from seawater. Limnology and Oceanography: Methods. 2008 Jun;6(6):230-5. doi:10.4319/lom.2008.6.230.</p>",
