                        },
                        "description": "<p>Metabolic profiles were obtained by injecting 1&nbsp;\u00b5L of each leachate extract (above) on a LC-(Ultimate 3000) Q-Exactive (MS) system (Thermo Fisher Scientific). Separations were achieved on a Accucore C18 column (100 x 2.1&nbsp;mm, 2.6&nbsp;\u00b5m, Thermo Fisher Scientific) by using a mobile phase of A: Water (with 0.1% formic acid (FA) and 0.2% acetonitrile); and B: Acetonitrile (with 0.1% FA) as follows: 0.0-0.2&nbsp;min 100% (v/v) A isocratic, 0.2-8.0&nbsp;min a gradient to 100% (v/v) B, 8.0-11.0&nbsp;min 100% (v/v) B isocratic, 11.0-12.0&nbsp;min a gradient to 100% (v/v) A, 12.1-14&nbsp;min 100% (v/v) A isocratic. The flow rate was set to 400&nbsp;\u00b5L/min.</p>",
